reason.tex:
%text Function composition is the act of applying one function $f(x)$ on another function $g(x)$ to \underline\text{produce a} \underline\text{third function - $h(x)$}
Mathematically, this is written as \[ \qquad h(x) = f\left[ g(x) \right] = (f\circ g)(x) \]
Note that \[ \qquad (f\circ g)(x) \neq (g\circ f)(x) \]
A \underline\text{couple of examples} should help clarify the concept
% \begin{tabular}{c|c|c|c} \hline f(x) & g(x) & (f\circ g)(x) & (g\circ f)(x) \\ \hline x^2 & \sin x & (\sin x)^2 = \sin^2 x& \sin x^2 \\ \hline \tan x & \sqrt{x} & \tan\sqrt{x} & \sqrt{\tan x} \\ \hline \end{tabular}
